			<tr>
				<td colspan="2" height="100%" valign="top"><span class="postbody">We now have a channel specific to the bufflist that people should be joining.
<br />

<br />
Melee positioning is very important. If you are not a rogue don't be behind a mob unless it is specified. If you are not MA do no not be in front of the mob unless a push to disrupt casting/gating is called. 
<br />

<br />
All other melee should be balancing the mob by taking positions on it's sides unless we are pinning a mob and then all on one side. Drift occurs during a fight and we have to adjust to it so that the mob doesn't roll over the MA, the MA isn't pushed out of heal range etc... 
<br />

<br />
Be aware of the mob and it's movement and adjust your position on the mob to stop drift. Circle strafing is a good technique for this, if the mob is moving forward move to it's front, the opposite for moving away from the MA. If we tell you to push a mob one way or another get into a position 45 degrees opposite the side we want him to go until he is in position then balance out to hold him there.</span><br /><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
