				<td colspan="2" height="100%" valign="top"><span class="postbody">Sup Proles, thought I would make a list of useful hotkeys for yall; these are primarily for Warriors/Tanks but there are some in this bunch that you lil Squishies can use.
<br />

<br />
For the majority of these I am going to use my personal hotkeys as example. Many of these can be personalized; there are, however, a few exceptions. A point to note: NO unnecessary spam, keep your Raid and Chat channel keys Short, Direct, and Easy to read.
<br />

<br />
We will start off with the really essential, easy, ones.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">/ass tanks name here</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
-Assist MT/2T/3T if I have to tell you this one, youre probably applying to the wrong guild. Everyone needs to ahve these keys, not just tanks, furthermore, know who each tank in the order is, fix your keys if that order changes.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Offtanking &lt;     Mob     &gt; Offtanking</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
-Offtanking key, as an app you will probably be using this one fairly often as we feel you out. Individuality has been squashed this now follows a strict outline, please notice the format...
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">ASSIST me with &lt;~&gt; Mob &lt;~&gt; Kill it NOW! </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
-Another key that could use some personalization, do not get too elaborate, but make it yours.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">&lt;{ ~ Going in 10 Seconds START CH Rotation on FELL ~  }&gt;</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
-A requirement for MTing, clerics need to know when to start their rota and it gives everyone a last warning before the fight starts. Personalizable, stay brief though.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">GAINING AGRO on this ~&lt;{ Mob }&gt;~ ! HEALS to FELL </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
-This key is almost never used, great for when the MT drop however, it lets the healers know who is next up for their heals. Another use is when we are setting up agro and CC other mobs in some of the more complicated encounters.
<br />
 
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">SPELLSHIELD Down -- SPELLSHIELD on FELL</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
-Another rarely used, but very important key, helps to mitigate some of the damage from the ungodly huge procs of certain mobs.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">CAUSTIC MIST has Gone &lt;~&gt; OFF &lt;~&gt; RUN in now and &lt;~(( JOUST for 10 SECONDS ONLY! ))~&gt;
<br />
/pause 100
<br />
CAUSTIC MIST INC &lt;~(( HIDE NOW ))~&gt; </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
-Giving you an example of one of our more in-depth hotkeys, not many are like this since there are few encounters that require them. Recognize the encounters that need these hotkeys and have one prepared before it is actually needed.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">AE AE &lt;~&gt; AE Has Gone OFF Nuke NOW &lt;~&gt; AE AE</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
- Not used often anymore, good to have created though.
<br />

<br />
~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~
<br />

<br />
The following Hotkeys follow a strict outline that must be adhered to. If not Freedom will flip out and probably die from internal hemorrhaging, please try not to make that happen, some people may be sad  :cry: 
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Rampage -- FELL -- Rampage </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
-If you take rampage damage you must use this key, everyone should have this key made and ready. On a side note, know which mobs rampage, and which ae rampage. If you are taking ae rampage, do not use this key, get out of ae rampage range and ask for a heal using the following key...
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">/say Heal Me -- FELL -- Heal Me</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">/say Cursed -- FELL -- Cursed</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">/say Diseased -- FELL -- Diseased</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">/say Poisoned -- FELL -- Poisoned</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
-Notice that each of these keys goes to the say channel, these keys should never be in the main raid channel, spam kills.</span><br /><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
