			<tr>
				<td colspan="2" height="100%" valign="top"><span class="postbody">End,
<br />

<br />
Anything in the above post that isnt stated as otherwise going to /say goes into the raid channel. Almost all MT/RT or Offtank calls go into the raid channel. If someone is assigned to call an AE that is actually timed or Spellshield is down etc, they will be calling it in the raid channel as well.
<br />

<br />
Some healers, who's name I wont mention here so they dont get spammed on raids prefer when you ask for a heal in /say to also tie that to a /tell to someone who has fast heals.
<br />

<br />
Something along the lines of:
<br />

<br />
/say Heal me -- yourname -- Heal me
<br />
/pause 2
<br />
/tell Random_Healer_01 Heal me -- yourname
<br />

<br />
This allows them to /rt and hit their quick heals. Far too often people think that they are bugging people when they spam asking for heals. I will say its far more annoying to hold up a raid to rebuff people, and waste even more mana on buffs than it is to heal them quickly and keep moving =)
<br />

<br />
If you need specifics on something that hasnt been covered here drop me a tell in game anytime bud.
<br />

<br />
--Jimmay</span><br /><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
